      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a good start for the sensory stuff. I wanted to lean more into the \"gritty\" part of the drama though. Since it's a drama, there's usually some underlying tension or struggle in these kinds of settings. Instead of just the loud/happy vibe, can you add some details that reflect the harder realities or the more common stresses that might be present in a household like that? Like, maybe some subtle hints about the neighborhood or the socioeconomic pressure they're dealing with?",
